Section 1:
1 L.D. 1257
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 AGRICULTURE, CONSERVATION AND FORESTRY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 832, L.D. 1257, “An Act Regarding
10 Labeling of Genetically Engineered Food Products”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Ban the Sale of Cell-cultured Meat'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §2163-A is enacted to read:
16 §2163-A. Sale of cell-cultured meat prohibited
17 1. Prohibition. A person within the State may not transport, receive for transportation,
18 sell or offer for sale or distribution any cell-cultured meat or products containing cell-
19 cultured meat or serve, expose or offer for sale or distribution, either in any public place or
20 elsewhere, any cell-cultured meat or products containing cell-cultured meat. For purposes
21 of this section, "cell-cultured meat" means any meat or food product produced from
22 cultured animal cells.
23 2. Inspection. The commissioner shall by adequate inspection see that the
24 requirements of this section are carried out.
25 3. Penalties. A person that violates any provision of this section commits a civil
26 violation for which a fine of not more than $100 for the first offense and a fine of not more
27 than $200 for each subsequent offense must be adjudged. The District Court and Superior
28 Court have concurrent jurisdiction of the offense.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment bans the sale or distribution of cell-cultured meat. The amendment
3333 defines cell-cultured meat as any meat or food product produced from cultured animal cells.
Page 1 - 132LR2196(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 832, L.D. 1257
314 The amendment provides that a person who violates the ban on the sale or distribution of
325 cell-cultured meat commits a civil violation for which a fine of not more than $100 for the
336 first offense and a fine of not more than $200 for each subsequent offense must be
347 adjudged.
358 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
369 (See attached)
